2026-05-17 05:42:31 | DEBUG | strands_evaluation.instrumentation.agent_plugins | Model response #4 [role=assistant block=1 tool_use] execute_ideal({"intent": "Filter to non-excluded serous tumor samples and compute median linear variants per Mbp (convert from log2 scale).", "code": "import pandas as pd, numpy as np\n\n# Load clinical meta and mutation burden from the same Excel source where mutation burden log2 is present.\nclinical_s3 = 's3://sana-kramabench/datagov/kramabench-biomedical-easy-2/files/1-s2.0-S0092867420301070-mmc1.xlsx'\nmut_s3 = 's3://sana-kramabench/datagov/kramabench-biomedical-hard-5/files/1-s2.0-S0092867420301070-mmc7.xlsx'\n\nclinical = pd.read_excel(clinical_s3, sheet_name='UCEC_CPTAC3_meta_table_V2.1')\n\n# Determine column names for serous and exclusion\n# Case_excluded likely is 'Case_excluded'. Histologic_type indicates serous.\n\nserous = clinical[(clinical['Case_excluded'].str.lower()!='yes') & (clinical['Histologic_type'].str.lower()=='serous')].copy()\n\n# Map sample ids: mutation burden uses idx like S001 corresponding to Proteomics? In clinical idx column is 'idx'.\nids = set(serous['idx'].astype(str))\n\n# Load mutation burden sheet\nmut = pd.read_excel(mut_s3, sheet_name='B-APM subtypes')\n\nmut.columns = [str(c) for c in mut.columns]\nmut = mut[mut['idx'].astype(str).isin(ids)].copy()\n\n# Convert log2 variants/Mbp to linear variants/Mbp\nmut['linear_variants_per_Mbp'] = np.power(2.0, mut['Log2_variant_per_Mbp'].astype(float))\n\nmedian_val = float(mut['linear_variants_per_Mbp'].median())\nprint(round(median_val,4))\n", "dataset_id": "kramabench-biomedical-easy-2"}) [toolUseId=call_W8hJmIja1hQ4UIukJDFNyIne]
